The United States and Germany have a strong partnership and work together on various issues. They are committed to policies that support global economic recovery and are negotiating the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (T-TIP) agreement to boost growth and create jobs. They also collaborate on education and training initiatives to strengthen economic and social growth. Germany is the largest economy in Europe and the US's top trading partner in the European Union. They are NATO allies and have worked together to oppose Russia's actions in Ukraine. They coordinate on security issues, counterterrorism, and multilateral concerns. They are leaders in international efforts to address climate change. The US and Germany have strong connections among citizens, with millions of Germans visiting the US and vice versa each year. They also have extensive academic, professional, and cultural exchange programs. The partnership between the two countries is rooted in shared values and a commitment to democracy, human rights, and the rule of law.